emmylua-debugger provides a high-performance cross-platform Lua debugger library.

## Installation options

### Default (Lua 5.4)
```
vcpkg install emmylua-debugger
```

### LuaJIT support
```
vcpkg install emmylua-debugger[luajit,-lua54]
```

## Platform-specific usage:

### Windows
Provides both emmy_tool.exe and emmy_core library:

1. Using the standalone tool:
   Run emmy_tool.exe from tools/emmylua-debugger/

2. Using the library in Lua:
   local dbg = require('emmy_core')
   dbg.tcpConnect('localhost', 9966)

### macOS and Linux
Provides emmy_core library only (no standalone tool):

1. Load the debugger module:
   local dbg = require('emmy_core')

2. Start debugging session:
   dbg.tcpConnect('localhost', 9966)

3. Connect your IDE (Visual Studio Code, IntelliJ IDEA, etc.) to port 9966

For CMake projects embedding the debugger:

    find_package(emmylua-debugger CONFIG REQUIRED)
    target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE emmylua-debugger::emmylua-debugger)